      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Concept ACK\r\n\r\nThis can be tested by cloning https://github.com/riscv-collab/riscv-gnu-toolchain, then:\r\n```\r\n./configure --prefix=/opt/riscv-ilp32 --with-arch=rv32gc --with-abi=ilp32\r\nmake\r\n```\r\nAnd then from the root directory:\r\n```\r\n/opt/riscv-ilp32/bin/riscv32-unknown-elf-g++ -std=c++20 -march=rv32i -mabi=ilp32 -I /path/to/bitcoin/src -c src/script/interpreter.cpp -o script.o\r\n```\r\n\r\nWithout this patch:\r\n```\r\nsrc/script/interpreter.cpp:1306:24: error: call of overloaded 'Serialize(HashWriter&, int)' is ambiguous\r\n 1306 |             ::Serialize(s, int{0});\r\n      |             ~~~~~~~~~~~^~~~~~~~~~~\r\n```\r\nWith this patch: Compiles successfully\r\n\r\nIf this patch is accepted, should this be backported to the 27 and 26 branches so libconsensus actually gets the patch while we figure out how to eventually support this platform through the kernel library?",
